race.comment: CRIMSON MISS (12) is a promising mare who finished strongly when resuming from a spell to grab third, just a length off the winner, over 1300m at Hawkesbury nearly 4 weeks ago. She won her only start here and can take this out. POINT SCORE (9) battled on late for fifth over 1200m in the Wyong Magic Millions 3&4yo Classic just over 3 weeks ago. His form prior was very good, and back in a more suitable grade, he will be hard to hold out. NAMASTE (2) kicked off this prep with a win two runs back but was less effective last start, finishing at the rear of the field over 1300m at Randwick, after being trapped wide throughout. He cops a wide gate, but is a promising colt with more to offer. Stick with him. FAST TRACK (14) is close to breaking through after two recent placings, the latest a second over 1400m at Hawkesbury. The blinkers go on, and she can go one better. APOLLO MISSION (1) has won 4 times on his home track here, and is still a chance, even after drawing very wide. Include.
